article.description: Mike Crawford scored 17 points, Miles Reynolds scored 16, and Saint Louis pulled away in the second half to beat Hartford 85-68 in its season opener on Sunday.
article.headline: Saint Louis pulls away from Hartford 85-68
article.linkText: Saint Louis pulls away from Hartford 85-68
article.story: ST. LOUIS, Mo. -- Mike Crawford scored 17 points, Miles Reynolds scored 16, and Saint Louis pulled away in the second half to beat Hartford 85-68 in its season opener on Sunday. Ash Yacoubou and Milik Yarbrough scored 13 each and Reggie Agbeko added 11 for the Billikens. Saint Louis opened with a 16-2 run, but Hartford (1-1) replied with a 14-2 run and Pancake Thomas tied it at 18 with a 3-pointer. Justin Graham's 3-pointer put the Hawks up 31-30, but Yarbrough sank a layup and free throw amid a 7-1 run and Saint Louis led 37-32 at halftime. Yarbrough capped a 12-2 run with a layup to open the second half and the Billikens led by 12 after Reynolds hit two free throws with 2:59 left. Thomas, one of three transfers who were forced to sit out last season due to NCAA transfer rules, scored 15 for the Hawks, Graham scored 13 and John Carroll, 12.
